Banque Saudi Lowers Bad-Loan Provisions By 72% in Second Quarter

-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 
2011-07-27T09:59:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-27/banque-saudi-lowers-bad-loan-provisions-by-72-in-second-quarter.html
Banque Saudi Fransi (BSFR) , a Saudi lender
part-owned by  Credit Agricole SA (ACA) , lowered provisions for bad
loans in the second quarter by 72 percent.  Provisions declined to 23.5 million riyals ($6.2 million)
in the three months ended June 30 from 83.9 million riyals a
year earlier, according to data posted on the  Saudi bourse 
website today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in Riyadh at 
 mharoutunian@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at   shajimathew@bloomberg.net  